dataIdInfo.idAbs: This layer contains land use information for the CSULB campus. The vector data for this basemap was primarily created through heads-up digitizing of aerial imagery acquired in 2011 through the Los Angelese Region Imagery Acquisition Consortium (LARIAC) with some limited fieldwork for ground truthing. The aerial imagery that served as the foundation for this basemap has 4" spatial resolution and the georefencing accuracy has been professionally tested and certified within .743 feet with 95% confidence.
